# Corp Web Design Alignment (TMaaS)

Marketing pages (`/`, `/marketplace`, `/service/:id`) must match `DQ_CORPWEB_PROTOTYPE` design language.

## Tokens & Typography
- Body font: **Plus Jakarta Sans** (`font-sans`), not Inter
- Brand colors: `text-dq-navy` (#030F35), `text-dq-orange` (#FB5535)
- Headings: `font-semibold`, not `font-bold`; hero up to `lg:text-8xl`
- Eyebrow labels: `font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-dq-orange`

## Layout Rhythm
- Section padding: `py-24 px-5 md:px-8 lg:px-10`
- Content max-width: `max-w-[1200px] mx-auto` (heroes may use `max-w-7xl`)
- Alternate backgrounds: `white` / `bg-gray-50`

## Components
- Navbar: static `sticky top-0 h-16`, no scroll-morph pill effect
- Cards: `rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 hover:border-dq-orange hover:shadow-xl transition-all duration-300`
- CTAs: `rounded-full`; primary navy (`bg-dq-navy`) or orange (`bg-dq-orange`); secondary glass (`bg-white/60 backdrop-blur-sm border`)
- Hero backgrounds: `MeshSection` with `hero-grid` overlay and mesh CSS vars from `index.css`
- Footer section labels: `font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-gray-400`

## Do Not
- Reintroduce morphing navbar or Inter as default body font
- Use `rounded-xl` + `border-navy-100` for marketing cards when corp web pattern applies
- Change page logic/routing when doing styling-only alignment work
